<paragraph id="982D36839972FF9DFF5BFBE0FA1D4198" blockId="1.[151,1437,1136,1773]" pageId="1" pageNumber="544">
This species was originally described from Harar, 
<collectingCountry id="E08576139972FF9DFD19FBE0FCB741C0" box="[725,823,1136,1161]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="1" pageNumber="544">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
, based on a single female specimen (
<bibRefCitation id="FC034B729972FF9DFB12FBE0FA1441C1" author="Hampson" box="[1246,1428,1136,1160]" pageId="1" pageNumber="544" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1919) A classification of the Aegeriadae [sic] of the Oriental and Ethiopian Regions. Novitates Zoologicae, 26 (1), 46 - 119." type="journal article" year="1919">
Hampson, 
<number id="2E5A24A49972FF9DFA97FBE0FA1441C1" box="[1371,1428,1136,1160]" pageId="1" pageNumber="544" value="1919.0">1919</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and till now no additional specimens have been collected. The original description by Hampson fairly complete and we do not need to repeat it here. Unfortunetely, males, female genitalia and individual variability remain unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="982D36839972FF9DFF0BFB4CFDBE43EC" blockId="1.[151,1437,1136,1773]" pageId="1" pageNumber="544">
<emphasis id="AAE6EA919972FF9DFF0BFB4CFE5941BC" bold="true" box="[199,473,1244,1269]" pageId="1" pageNumber="544">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
By its coloration and completely opaque wings this species belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="5F924D009972FF9DFF5BFA91FEC44051" box="[151,324,1281,1304]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Melittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="544" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aureosquamata">
<emphasis id="AAE6EA919972FF9DFF5BFA91FEC44051" box="[151,324,1281,1304]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="544">aureosquamata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group. From 
<taxonomicName id="5F924D009972FF9DFDF6FA91FC6E4050" authority="Wallengren, 1863" authorityName="Wallengren" authorityYear="1863" box="[570,1006,1280,1305]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Melittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="544" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aureosquamata">
<emphasis id="AAE6EA919972FF9DFDF6FA91FC8C4051" box="[570,780,1281,1304]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="544">M. aureosquamata</emphasis>
(Wallengren, 
<number id="2E5A24A49972FF9DFC60FA90FC654050" box="[940,997,1280,1305]" pageId="1" pageNumber="544" value="1863.0">1863</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="5F924D009972FF9DFC39FA91FB2F4051" box="[1013,1199,1280,1304]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Melittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="544" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abyssiniensis">
<emphasis id="AAE6EA919972FF9DFC39FA91FB2F4051" box="[1013,1199,1280,1304]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="544">M. abyssiniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by minute details in the coloration of the hind leg tuft. It is possible, as was stated before in 
<bibRefCitation id="FC034B729972FF9DFB04FAB4FF634029" author="Gorbunov" pageId="1" pageNumber="544" refString="Gorbunov, O. G. &amp; Arita, Y. (1997) A revision of Ferdinand Le Cerf's clearwing moth types (Lepidoptera, Sesiidae), kept at the Paris Museum. II. Melittiini in the Afrotropical Region. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology, 3 (2), 289 - 323." type="journal article" year="1997">
Gorbunov &amp; Arita (
<number id="2E5A24A49972FF9DFF53FAD8FF5B4029" box="[159,219,1352,1376]" pageId="1" pageNumber="544" value="1997.0">1997</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, that the latter species may be a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="5F924D009972FF9DFCD3FAD9FC714029" box="[799,1009,1353,1376]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Melittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="544" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aureosquamata">
<emphasis id="AAE6EA919972FF9DFCD3FAD9FC714029" box="[799,1009,1353,1376]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="544">M. aureosquamata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. From 
<taxonomicName id="5F924D009972FF9DFB8EFAD9FAF34029" authority="Le Cerf, 1917" authorityName="Le Cerf" authorityYear="1917" box="[1090,1395,1352,1377]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Melittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="544" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="houlberti">
<emphasis id="AAE6EA919972FF9DFB8EFAD9FB4D4029" box="[1090,1229,1352,1376]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="544">M. houlberti</emphasis>
Le Cerf, 
<number id="2E5A24A49972FF9DFAF4FAD8FAF34029" box="[1336,1395,1352,1376]" pageId="1" pageNumber="544" value="1917.0">1917</number>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="5F924D009972FF9DFAB1FAD9FEAB40CD" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Melittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="544" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abyssiniensis">
<emphasis id="AAE6EA919972FF9DFAB1FAD9FEAB40CD" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="544">M. abyssiniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by the coloration of the hind tibia (dark brown to black with bronze sheen, with a narrow orange stripe dorsally from base of tibia to base of mid spurs in the species compared) and hind tarsus (dark brown to black with strong bronze-green sheen in 
<taxonomicName id="5F924D009972FF9DFDB2FA25FC8B4085" box="[638,779,1460,1484]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Melittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="544" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="houlberti">
<emphasis id="AAE6EA919972FF9DFDB2FA25FC8B4085" box="[638,779,1460,1484]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="544">M. houlberti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="AAE6EA919972FF9DFCD5FA25FCBA4085" box="[793,826,1461,1484]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="544">cp.</emphasis>
<figureCitation id="00A92A069972FF9DFC8EFA24FC034085" box="[834,899,1460,1485]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1618,1641]" captionTargetBox="[161,1416,273,1580]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,257,1597]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Melittia spp.: 1) M. abyssiniensis Hampson, 1919, ♀ holotype. Alar expanse 36.0 mm; 2) ditto, labels; 3) M. pyropis Hampson, 1919, ♀ holotype. Alar expanse 42.0 mm; 4) ditto, labels; 5) M. endoxantha Hampson, 1919, ♀ holotype. Alar expanse 34.0 mm; 6) ditto, labels." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237992/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="544">
Fig. 
<number id="2E5A24A49972FF9DFCB9FA24FC034085" box="[885,899,1460,1484]" pageId="1" pageNumber="544" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
with fig. 
<quantity id="5F6A9B669972FF9DFC3DFA24FB9D4084" box="[1009,1053,1460,1485]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.286" pageId="1" pageNumber="544" unit="in" value="9.0">9 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="FC034B729972FF9DFBE8FA24FAA64085" author="Gorbunov" box="[1060,1318,1460,1485]" pageId="1" pageNumber="544" refString="Gorbunov, O. G. &amp; Arita, Y. (1997) A revision of Ferdinand Le Cerf's clearwing moth types (Lepidoptera, Sesiidae), kept at the Paris Museum. II. Melittiini in the Afrotropical Region. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology, 3 (2), 289 - 323." type="journal article" year="1997">
Gorbunov, Arita, 
<number id="2E5A24A49972FF9DFB26FA24FAA64085" box="[1258,1318,1460,1484]" pageId="1" pageNumber="544" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). From 
<taxonomicName id="5F924D009972FF9DFAB1FA25FE0540B9" authority="Le Cerf, 1914" authorityName="Le Cerf" authorityYear="1914" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Melittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="544" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="azrael">
<emphasis id="AAE6EA919972FF9DFAB1FA25FF5D40B9" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="544">M. azrael</emphasis>
Le Cerf, 
<number id="2E5A24A49972FF9DFE86FA48FE0540B9" box="[330,389,1496,1520]" pageId="1" pageNumber="544" value="1914.0">1914</number>
</taxonomicName>
, this species clearly differs by the coloration of the vertex (brown to dark brown with bronze sheen, with a few orange and black scales in 
<taxonomicName id="5F924D009972FF9DFD63FA6DFC9E435D" box="[687,798,1532,1556]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Melittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="544" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="azrael">
<emphasis id="AAE6EA919972FF9DFD63FA6DFC9E435D" box="[687,798,1532,1556]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="544">M. azrael</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), thorax (both meso- and metathorax dark brown with bronze sheen in the species compared), hind leg tuft (without orange scales in the species compared) and by the coloration of the wings (dark brown with strong golden-green sheen in 
<taxonomicName id="5F924D009972FF9DFC38F9D5FBE54315" box="[1012,1125,1604,1628]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Melittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="544" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="azrael">
<emphasis id="AAE6EA919972FF9DFC38F9D5FBE54315" box="[1012,1125,1604,1628]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="544">M. azrael</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="AAE6EA919972FF9DFBB4F9D5FB134315" box="[1144,1171,1605,1628]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="544">cp</emphasis>
. 
<figureCitation id="00A92A069972FF9DFB6AF9D4FB6E4315" box="[1190,1262,1604,1629]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1618,1641]" captionTargetBox="[161,1416,273,1580]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,257,1597]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Melittia spp.: 1) M. abyssiniensis Hampson, 1919, ♀ holotype. Alar expanse 36.0 mm; 2) ditto, labels; 3) M. pyropis Hampson, 1919, ♀ holotype. Alar expanse 42.0 mm; 4) ditto, labels; 5) M. endoxantha Hampson, 1919, ♀ holotype. Alar expanse 34.0 mm; 6) ditto, labels." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237992/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="544">
